  {
    "type": "math",
    "content": "\\frac{d}{dx}[3x^2] = 3 \\cdot 2 \\cdot x^{2-1} = 6x",
    "narration": "First term \u2014 3x squared. The 2 comes down, multiplies the 3, and the exponent drops to 1. That gives us 6x.",
    "mode": "replace",
    "step": 3,
